{
  "text": "Gas-permeable cell culture devices (G-Rex) are being evaluated for the expansion of T cells and tumor cells. In these systems, gas exchange across the base of the culture allows increased volumes of medium per unit area, augments the rate of cell expansion, and decreases cell death, minimizing cell manipulation. Using this strategy, up to 19 \u00d7 10 9 functional NK cells were produced starting from leukapheresis products, within 8-10 days of culture [CITATION_1] . The contaminating T cells mostly comprised CD8",
